This paper is about training neural network acoustic models for speech recognition tasks, which falls under the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses discriminative training criteria and optimization techniques, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of different models, which could be considered as a subfield of statistical learning (cs.SD) and systems and control (cs.SI).
